    35→/**
    36→ * A {@link WindowAssigner} that windows elements into sessions based on market trading hours. This
    37→ * assigner groups trading events by market session boundaries (e.g., NYSE 09:30-16:00 ET) rather
    38→ * than fixed time intervals.
    39→ *
    40→ * <p>The window boundaries are determined by the market's open and close times in the specified
    41→ * timezone. Each element is assigned to the trading session containing its timestamp.
    42→ *
    43→ * <p>Windows can overlap and be merged using the standard {@link TimeWindow} merging logic.
    44→ *
